.TH SSHLS 1 "2026-07-13" "sshls 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sshls \- interactive SSH host selector built on fzf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sshls
.RI [ tag ]
.br
.B sshls
.B add
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sshls
lists the hosts defined in
.I ~/.ssh/config
and presents them in an
.BR fzf (1)
picker with a live preview of each host's config block. Selecting a host
opens an SSH connection to it.
.PP
With no argument, all hosts are shown. Given a
.IR tag ,
only hosts carrying that tag are shown.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI sshls " tag"
Show only hosts whose
.B # Tags:
comment includes
.IR tag .
.TP
.B sshls add
Interactively add a new host to
.IR ~/.ssh/config .
See
.BR "ADDING HOSTS" .
.SH KEY BINDINGS
Inside the picker:
.TP
.B Enter
Connect to the selected host.
.TP
.B Ctrl-A
Add a new host (equivalent to
.BR "sshls add" ).
.TP
.B Type
Fuzzy-search the list.
.TP
.B Escape ", " Ctrl-C
Exit without connecting.
.SH ADDING HOSTS
.B sshls add
(or Ctrl-A in the picker) prompts for the alias, HostName, User, Port,
IdentityFile, and Tags; Port, IdentityFile, and Tags are optional. Before
saving, a non-interactive connection test is run; on failure you are asked
whether to save anyway. The new host appears in the picker immediately.
.PP
If a field contains an inline bash-style range
.RB ( {start..end}
or
.BR {start..end..step} ),
the add flow expands it into one host per node. Padding follows the numbers
you write. Multiple ranged fields must expand to the same count and are
matched by position; non-ranged fields are copied to every node. All nodes are
connection-tested in parallel; you then choose to save all, only the passing
ones, or abort. Nodes whose alias already exists are skipped.
.SH TAGGING
Tag a host by placing a
.B # Tags:
comment immediately before its
.B Host
entry in
.IR ~/.ssh/config ,
with tags comma-separated:
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Tags: production, eu
Host web-eu-01
    HostName 1.eu.example.com
    User alice
.fi
.RE
.PP
Tags are shown next to the hostname in the picker. A host tagged
.B ignore
is hidden from the list entirely.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.ssh/config
The SSH client configuration that
.B sshls
reads hosts and tags from, and writes new hosts to.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.BR fzf (1),
.BR ssh (1),
.BR awk (1),
.BR column (1),
.BR sed (1),
.BR sort (1).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ssh (1),
.BR ssh_config (5),
.BR fzf (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Matej Jehlicka
